A Kisii court has ordered a police officer facing murder charges to undergo mental assessment.
Boniface Maubi was arrested and placed in custody on Wednesday evening and detectives from the Internal Affairs Unit Headquarters opened an investigation file for him.
The police officer is accused of attacking and seriously injuring a 38-year-old man held at Kisii Central Police Station who later died.



