The officer, in the company of his colleagues, is said to have assaulted Bramuel Chakunza last Saturday for violating the dusk-to-dawn curfew.
Mr Chakunza succumbed to injuries on Tuesday morning while receiving treatment at Nyanchwa Adventist Hospital.
Murder charge
The Directorate of Public Prosecutions later directed that Maubi, 36, be arrested and charged for murder.
The suspect will now return to the dock on January 7 for plea taking.



