He was brought to court under tight security on Thursday morning and arraigned before Kisii Resident Magistrate Dorcas Mac Andere but did not take plea.
The prosecution requested that the accused be detained for a week to allow him undergo mental assessment.
“The accused will be detained at Kisii Central Police Station for seven days and mental assement test done at Kisii Teaching and Referral Hospital,” said the magistrate.
Repair shop
The victim, a resident of Vihiga County, had been operating a phone repair shop in Central Kisii town and had only joined a friend who had gone to check on his wife who was in the cells when he was bundled into the cells where he was clobbered ruthlessly, police said.
The police officer was picked in a public identification parade.



